import React from 'react'
import {
    ServicesContainer,
    ColumnLeft,
    ColumnRight,
    ServicesH1,
    ServicesH2,
    ServicesP,
    ServicesWrapper,
    ServicesIcon, Mockup
} from './WheelyAppElements'
import Icon1 from '../../Images/1.svg'
import Icon2 from '../../Images/Vf.svg'
import Icon3 from '../../Images/Account.svg'
import mockup from "../../Images/profile.svg";
import {HeroP, HeroTitle} from "../Hero/HeroElements";

const Trading = () => {
    return (
        <>
            <ServicesContainer id="wheely-app">
                <ServicesH1>WHEELY APP</ServicesH1>
                <ServicesWrapper>
                    <ColumnLeft>
                        <HeroTitle>WHEELY IS A WEB 3 APPLICATION</HeroTitle>
                        <HeroP>Users can earn tokens by driving any mode of transport.
                        </HeroP>
                        <HeroP>Whether it's a bike, scooter, car, or even public transportation,
                        </HeroP>
                        <HeroP>you can earn game token.
                        </HeroP>
                        <ColumnRight>
                            <Mockup src={mockup} />
                        </ColumnRight>
                    </ColumnLeft>
                </ServicesWrapper>
            </ServicesContainer>
        </>
    )
}

export default Trading
